> Lemon brightens up any meal, and this dish is positively bursting with citrusy goodness! Paprika-coated chicken is drizzled with a creamy, lemon-and-thyme-spiked pan sauce that'd taste good on pretty much anything. On the side; tender roasted carrots and steamy rice with lemon zest and pistachios. When life gives you lemons, you know what to do.

== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Strip 1 tsp thyme leaves (2 tsp for 4 servings) from stems; finely chop leaves. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pistachio Rice ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Lemony Sauce ==

While rice cooks, pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @paprika{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

> Swap in salmon for chicken; cook (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken is browning too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for salmon over medium heat. Add chopped @thyme{¼%ounce}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer, then immediately turn off heat.

Stir in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest and @pistachios{½%ounce}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: For extra richness, stir in 1 TBSP butter; 2 TBSP for 4 servings.

Divide rice, carrots, and salmon between plates. Top salmon with sauce and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.